description:

Take advantage of our ONLINE APPLICATION PROCESS. You may submit your application online, fax, email or in person. We do not release information on the application activity and encourage you to apply if you are interested in this property. You will generally receive an email update on your application status within 1 business day after applying. If your application is not processed you will not be charged any fees.

Approved applicants are given 24hrs (1 business day) to place their deposit in order to hold the property and set a move in date. Please be sure to schedule a viewing of the property either before or immediately after submitting an application to rent.

New Heights in apartment living!

Nestled in the desirable Greenhaven Pocket area just off of I-5 and minutes from downtown Sacramento, The Davenport offers you the perfect mixture of convenience and location. Whether you want to spend your day on the water at Lake Greenhaven or the Sacramento River, in the park at Seymour Park or Bear Flag School Park, exploring downtown Sacramento or shopping and dining in some of Sacramento's finest locations, The Davenport puts you in close proximity to the best Sacramento has to offer in a location you'll be proud to call home. description:
The Renaissance wants to continue offering the same level of customer service, however due to the impact of COVID-19, we will be adjusting how apartment tours are conducted. We invite you to take a live virtual video tour with our leasing professionals. Contact us for more details! 

Leisure is a big part of life at The Renaissance in Citrus Heights. Our community is nestled within an area rich with natural beauty. Take in the greenery at Tempo Park or Cherry Creek Park, and take an invigorating walk or hike at Arcade Creek Park Reserve or the Sacramento Trail. For refined comforts, explore dining and shopping at the Sunrise Mall. Enjoy convenient access to nearby San Juan High School, Creative Frontiers Elementary, and Countryside Montessori.

The Renaissance has everything you need for comfortable, carefree living, including spacious, pet-friendly 1-, 2-, and 3-bedroom apartments and cottage-style homes with spacious closets, central heat and air, and patios or balconies. Our community offers an opportunity to live the good life, replete with a swimming pool, spa, full-size basketball court, fitness center, and BBQ and picnic area.

Enjoy rebates and get huge savings from your rent up to the first 3 months if you sign a lease with us on or before April 30, 2020. Call us now to book your showing!

Pleasant, 2 bedrooms, 1 bathroom apartment home property rental in a dynamic neighborhood in Sacramento. Community features include a fitness center, sports court, parks or playgrounds, and community pool.

The bright and unfurnished interior features tile/laminate floors, recessed lighting, windows with blinds, and a high vaulted ceiling. Additional rooms: living room and dining room. Smoking on the property is prohibited. It comes with an in-unit washer and dryer along with centralized A/C, gas and forced-air heating.

Tenant is responsible for electricity (Sacramento Municipal Utility District SMUD), gas (PG&E), internet, and cable (which the owner can install). The landlord will cover water, trash, and sewage.

Experience digital application at no cost, online payments, and efficient 24/7 maintenance support. Choose from a variety of tours - Self-Tours, Guided Tours, or 3D Virtual Tours. Enjoy this and more when you book today!

William Land Elementary School, Sutter Middle School, and C. K. McClatchy High School are nearby. 

Nearby Parks: Southside Park, O'Neil Park, Leland Stanford Mansion State Historic Park, and Crocker Park.

The property's Bike Score is 98/100. This is a Biker's Paradise and daily errands can be accomplished on a bike.

description:
Casa is a manufactured home community peacefully situated in the riverfront area of West Sacramento. The community offers a choice of well-appointed 1 and 2 bedroom homes, some new, located in a park-like setting that features spacious lots, a clubhouse, and a swimming pool. The commercial center provides a sandwich shop, car wash, and barber shop. Each of the homes has a yard and covered parking. Appliances include microwaves, dishwashers, garbage disposals, and air conditioners. There is a municipal community center and library across the street, and Casa is walking distance to local shops and restaurants. The community is also close to historic Old Town Sacramento and Raley Field, home to the AAA baseball River Cats.

The homes at Casa are continually being upgraded. Onsite management has a commitment to excellence and strives to provide an enjoyable tenancy for all the residents, based on a keen sense of community.

About West Sacramento: The area offers small-town charm, a business-friendly attitude, outstanding transportation access, and all the urban amenities of metro Sacramento, the state capital. There are a number of fine restaurants, wineries, and brew pubs in the region. Other leisure activities include fishing and boating on the Sacramento River, nature excursions in the Yolo Bypass Wildlife Area, and professional basketball and baseball. The University of California at Davis campus is just minutes away.

description:
Recently remodeled, this Midtown apartment is waiting for you! The spacious living area with the wood burning fireplace are among the features of this home. The upgraded kitchen has new granite counter tops and features both an eating bar and a separate dining area and yes the refrigerator is included. As for the bedrooms the master bedroom has a walk-in closet and access to the rear yard while the large secondary bedroom has great closet space. New carpet, flooring and fresh paint throughout. A rare find in Midtown is that this unit has an private outdoor living area. Perfect for relaxing after a long day. Enjoy convenient access to local shopping, community parks and everything Midtown has to offer. 

Tenants are responsible for 25% of the water, sewer, and trash billing each month.

This is a non-smoking home. You may apply online right from this page; just click the Apply Now button. 

Screening Guidelines:
1. All individuals planning on living at the property, over the age of 18, must apply. Application fee is $45.00 per adult.
2. A credit score of at least 650 is normally required.
3. Good rental references. No evictions, no exceptions.
4. A household monthly income of at least 3.25 times the monthly rent amount (or a verifiable cash reserves).
5. If self employed, documents for year-to-date income and past two years IRS 1040 are required.
6. No pets unless otherwise stated on the property page of our web site. If acceptable, an additional pet deposit is required for each pet.
7. Tenancy must start within 2 weeks from the approval of your application.

NOTE: We strongly encourage you to view the property prior to remitting an application. Applications will not be considered or processed until application fee(s) and all required documents have been submitted. Application fees are non-refundable.

Resident Satisfaction Programs: 
Quality air filters shipped to your door every 90 days to help save you 5-15% on your heating and cooling bill as well as create a clean healthy living environment for $10.00 per month. Note additional charge of $10.00 per month applies for all properties with HVAC systems for our HVAC Maintenance Reduction Program. We want your rental experience to be a delight that treats you with the respect and attentiveness you deserve. Whether you're dealing with a maintenance emergency or have general questions regarding your home, we want to provide you with an immediate response 24/7/365. Weekend, holidays, or middle of the night, we want you to have the help you need. To give you the care and attention that you deserve, we've chosen to partner with a company called Latchel to offer you a 24/7 Home Assistant for $14.99 per month. Not only do you get a personal home assistant 24/7, they cover some Tenant maintenance fees that may arise during a tenancy. Brochure with full details available.

-Tenant credit score of at least 680 with no unpaid liens or collections
-No bankruptcy, foreclosure, or judgments in last 3 years
-Tenant combined gross monthly income equal to at least 3x monthly rent
-Minimum 1 year with current employer
-No evictions in past 5 years
-Tenant has minimum 3 years verifiable good rental history with Current & Previous Landlord

An application fee is required for each application as a processing fee to verify income, credit, and eviction history. The fee is non-refundable once the application processing has begun. We accept payment for processing online by credit card. Walk down the hall to find 3 bedrooms with nice sized closets and 2 full baths. The master suite offers 2 closets with mirrored doors and an en suite bathroom. The formal dining area leads to the open kitchen with walk-in pantry, electric range, dishwasher, garbage disposal, refrigerator and breakfast bar. The second living room with oversized patio door allows an abundance of natural sunlight to shine through. The private backyard is great for a small garden and has a a concrete patio, great for entertainment! The washer (only) is conveniently located in the garage. Located near parks, freeway access and shopping, you will not want to miss this opportunity!

5. A household monthly income of at least 3 times the monthly rent amount (or a verifiable cash reserves).
6. No Pets unless otherwise stated on the property page of our web site.
7. Rent must normally start within 2 weeks from the approval of your application.

Fully furnished home perfect for local professionals and students with family and pets! You'll get a private garage for 2 cars, ample street parking, and a fully-equipped kitchen. All bedrooms are fully furnished with comfortable, foam mattress beds. 5 total bedrooms and 3 full bathrooms offer generous living space for the whole family. The master suite features an ensuite bathroom. The property features an expansive, paved backyard and an extra tall car port to park several vehicles, RV, or boat. The detached garage is oversized and makes for the perfect workshop. The home is equipped with smart Wifi thermostats to adjust temperature from your phone and smart locks for both front and back doors so you never have to worry about forgetting keys. A separate laundry room is equipped with a washer and dryer. Located just south of the East Sacramento area, the home is near the intersection of the 50 and 99 freeways. You'll be within walking distance of Target and biking distance to UC Davis Medical Center and Sacramento State University.

description:
Seeking Special Renters for Rare Old Fair Oaks Treasure! 
Second Floor unit, 2 BR, 2 Spa Baths, 2 Fireplaces, Private Parking, Patio overlooking Atrium, Periscope- yes, you read that right! Solar Roof, Pet Friendly, Minutes from River Views & Bike Trail.

This is the best appointed home in Old Fair Oaks, right across the street from Village Park. Living room has lots of natural light and vaulted ceilings with a unique fan that'll make every day feel like you're on vacation. Small workspace or breakfast nook built into kitchen
Separate staircase entrance and your very own parking spot on alley.

Convenient location to major freeways (Hwy 50), shopping, and recreation! Down the street from larger shopping centers, including Trader Joe's & Bel Air.

Front row seats on large wrap-around front patio overlooking park & stage for festivals & concerts in the spring/summer.

Your sanctuary awaits.

description:
Rivercrest offers 328 well-designed apartment homes on a lushly landscaped and waterscaped 20-acre site providing a wealth of amenities. All the spacious residences include private patios/balconies, separate dining areas, walk-in closets, modern gourmet kitchens, storage, and attractive fixtures. Many also offer vaulted ceilings, linen closets, and stylish two-tone decor. Choose from three different floor plans, including 1-bedroom and 2-bedroom apartments as well as 3-bedroom, 2-bath units boasting twin balconies with views. Centrally located in vibrant Sacramento, Rivercrest is only seven miles from downtown, near public bus and light-rail routes, and walking distance to Sacramento State University and the American River greenbelt. 

There are many ways for residents to keep fit and have fun at Rivercrest. They can take advantage of Rivercrest's four swimming pools, heated hydro-spa, four lighted tennis courts, club-like fitness room with TV, basketball and sand volleyball courts, picnic/barbeque area, and children's playground. The club house and resident lounge host a complimentary computer-equipped business center, Wi-Fi connections, billiards, and a free tanning salon and yoga classes. In addition, there are six 24-hour laundry rooms on the premises. 

About Sacramento: Founded during the California Gold Rush, Sacramento is the state's capital and sixth largest city. The Sacramento metro region is home to a diverse population of more than 2.5 million. Higher education institutions in the area include Sacramento State University, the nearby Davis campus of the University of California, three community colleges, Pacific McGeorge School of Law, and a number of private colleges. Among local attractions are the quaint Old Town district, Sutter's Fort Historic Park, the state railroad museum, 5,000 acres of parkland, and numerous cultural and arts activities throughout the year. The Sierra Nevada Gold Country, with its many outdoor recreation destinations and wineries, is just a short drive away.

description:
Greetings! I have two separate bedrooms available for rent in my 3 bed/2 bath home. Make this place your own! Bring a friend and receive $100 off first month's rent if both accepted! 

Each room is $780/month, which includes utilities, internet, garbage, water, and landscaping. This is a great deal for a beautiful home. See below for details.

The house is conveniently located right on the border of the up-and-coming North Oak Park neighborhood in Sacramento. We are within walking distance to Broadway's new restaurants, bars, coffee shops, theater, brewery, parks, and farmers market. The street has many cute, revitalized homes and super friendly neighbors. UC Davis Medical Center, Pacific McGeorge Law School, Sac City College, and the DMV are just around the corner, and less than 10 minutes from Sac State. Easy freeway access leads to 2-minute drive to midtown and all its activities and amenities. The neighborhood truly is a hidden gem, inspired by diversity, co-existence, and community.

It boasts a large porch, bay windows, charming original details, hardwood floors, high ceilings, dishwasher, new paint and hardware, central heat/air, cute curb appeal, laundry and updated kitchen and bathrooms. The home has eco-conscious and money-saving features, including 100% green renewable energy, tank-less water heater, and low-flow toilets and faucets.The basement is absolutely massive with ample space for storage. I also intend to create raised garden beds in the side yard in the near future.

description:
Casa is a manufactured home community peacefully situated in the riverfront area of West Sacramento. The community offers a choice of well-appointed 1 and 2 bedroom homes, some new, located in a park-like setting that features spacious lots, a clubhouse, and a swimming pool. The commercial center provides a sandwich shop, car wash, and barber shop. Each of the homes has a yard and covered parking. Appliances include microwaves, dishwashers, garbage disposals, and air conditioners. There is a municipal community center and library across the street, and Casa is walking distance to local shops and restaurants. The community is also close to historic Old Town Sacramento and Raley Field, home to the AAA baseball River Cats.

The homes at Casa are continually being upgraded. Onsite management has a commitment to excellence and strives to provide an enjoyable tenancy for all the residents, based on a keen sense of community.

About West Sacramento: The area offers small-town charm, a business-friendly attitude, outstanding transportation access, and all the urban amenities of metro Sacramento, the state capital. There are a number of fine restaurants, wineries, and brew pubs in the region. Other leisure activities include fishing and boating on the Sacramento River, nature excursions in the Yolo Bypass Wildlife Area, and professional basketball and baseball. The University of California at Davis campus is just minutes away.

description:
Casa is a manufactured home community peacefully situated in the riverfront area of West Sacramento. The community offers a choice of well-appointed 1 and 2 bedroom homes, some new, located in a park-like setting that features spacious lots, a clubhouse, and a swimming pool. The commercial center provides a sandwich shop, car wash, and barber shop. Each of the homes has a yard and covered parking. Appliances include microwaves, dishwashers, garbage disposals, and air conditioners. There is a municipal community center and library across the street, and Casa is walking distance to local shops and restaurants. The community is also close to historic Old Town Sacramento and Raley Field, home to the AAA baseball River Cats.

The homes at Casa are continually being upgraded. Onsite management has a commitment to excellence and strives to provide an enjoyable tenancy for all the residents, based on a keen sense of community.

About West Sacramento: The area offers small-town charm, a business-friendly attitude, outstanding transportation access, and all the urban amenities of metro Sacramento, the state capital. There are a number of fine restaurants, wineries, and brew pubs in the region. Other leisure activities include fishing and boating on the Sacramento River, nature excursions in the Yolo Bypass Wildlife Area, and professional basketball and baseball. The University of California at Davis campus is just minutes away.

Near Meadowview Road and Freeport Boulevard in South Sacramento, this remodeled, one story, single family home offers three bedrooms and two bathrooms. The dining nook has linoleum flooring, overhead ceiling fan and a door to the laundry room.

The kitchen has linoleum flooring, oak cabinets, granite counters and backsplash, and is equipped with:

frost-free mini-refrigerator
glass top electric range with self cleaning oven
dishwasher
double stainless steel sink with garbage disposal and convertible faucet

The master bedroom has laminate flooring and a double door closet. The master bathroom has linoleum flooring and a walk-in shower with glass door. The second bedroom has laminate flooring, overhead lighting and a double door closet. The third bedroom has laminate flooring and a double door closet. The hall bath has linoleum flooring and a shower over tub.

There are security doors on the front and rear doors. The laundry area has electrical hook-ups. The two-car garage has a storage closet, built-in shelving and comes with a remote door opener. The fenced rear yard has a large uncovered patio, children's play structure and gardening will be tenant responsibility. This home is located in the Sacramento Unified School District.

Yard maintenance is tenant responsibility.

description:
Historic Calvin E Crocker House. Stunning Colonial Revival Triplex in historic Alkali Flat neighborhood. Fully furnished main home welcomes you with a charming front porch, a formal main entrance with grand staircase, inlaid floors, high ceilings and period fixtures that brings you back to the turn of the century. 

Three bedrooms, three baths, separate office, with modern conveniences, internet, cable television, security system, four television sets, large garage, shared laundry, fireplace, linens, towels, huge kitchen, kitchenware, formal dining room; just bring your personal toiletries. Sleeps seven people; there are six twin sized beds and a roll out bed. Twin beds can be converted to king sized beds upon request. 

This historic and charming home was lovingly refurbished and expanded into a triplex with three separate apartments. The other two units are a ground level two bedroom/two bath, and, a one bedroom/one bath on the 4th floor known as the Crow?s Nest. Built in 1902, nestled between Midtown and Downtown Sacramento, close to restaurants, entertainment, public transportation, business, and State Capital.

Three blocks from Sacramento County Courthouse and City Hall, KCRA Television, and the new Sacramento Railyards Project. Seven Blocks from the California State Capital, California State Capitol Museum, the Sacramento Kings Arena Stadium Golden 1 Center, and the Downtown Commons. Twelve blocks to the California State Railroad Museum and Old Sacramento State Historic Park.

Six minute drive to The Crocker Art Museum, Raley Field, and the Blue Diamond Growers - Corporate Campus. Eight Minute Drive to Sutter General Hospital. Nine minute drive to the California State Fairgrounds. Ten minute Drive to UC Davis Medical Center. Eleven minute drive to McGeorge School of Law. Fifteen minute drive California State University, Sacramento.
Lease Details: Fully furnished. Owner pays water, electricity, sewer, cable and internet. Provides modern conveniences, internet, cable television, security system, four television sets, large garage, shared laundry, linens, towels, kitchenware. Sleeps seven people; there are six twin sized beds and a roll out bed. Twin beds can be converted to king sized beds upon request.

description:
Summary: Fully furnished private room and bath available for short term rent (3 -6 months), utilities included.

Curious what makes Sacramento a hidden gem? Live like a local and find out for yourself in this charming cottage home situated in the heart of Midtown, Sacramento. Boulevard Park was voted the #1 neighborhood for best places for young professionals in the Sacramento area per Niche. Blending modern conveniences with historic charm, the private room is part of a 100-year old cottage house perfectly situated to enjoy quiet walks along tree-lined streets to sample Sacramento's finest dining or our award-winning coffee shops. Known as the nation's farm-to-fork capital, the Sacramento area has been an agricultural powerhouse for more than a century, home to more than 40 regional farmers' markets. As the seasons change, so do local restaurant menus, giving you a true taste of local flavor. Those seeking high energy experiences are only a short walk away from local breweries and bars. 

Who am I? My name is Samson, a transplant from Virginia who has decided to plant his roots in Sacramento. I happily live with my partner, Cory, and Trixie (our loving terrier mix). We are both young professionals in our 20s. We welcome you into our home with open arms and warm hearts. 

Bedrooms/bathrooms: The private room (13x10) is fully furnished with a queen size bed, two nightstands, and large dresser. A private bathroom is available to the tenant. The room contains a large window for natural light and a decently sized closet perfect for storing your personal items and clothes. The rooms have hardwood flooring with central heat and air condition. 

Common space: Living room contains a large couch and ottoman along with a large 4K TV. If you love to cook, you will love the Bertazonni stove and spacious new refrigerator. All essential kitchenware is available to the tenant to use during their stay. 

Outdoor amenities: The backyard will be available for you to use, equipped with a beautiful wooden gazebo shaded by a large orange and lemon tree perfect for relaxing outside or enjoying a nice meal. Have a game of cornhole or workout on the open green astroturf. You can enjoy a glass a wine under the twinkle lights strung above. 

LGBTQ+ friendly.
Lease Details: Utilities included. 1 month deposit required.

Near Garfield Avenue and Whitney Avenue, Carmichael, this open one-story duplex offers two bedrooms and two bathrooms. This home has programmable central heat and air conditioning. The leaded glass, eight panel door opens onto laminate flooring, vaulted ceilings, custom paint and dual pane windows with two inch blinds and verticals throughout 1,128 square feet of living space. The living room has laminate flooring and a tile, wood-burning fireplace and hearth with glass doors. There is also a formal dining room with overhead lighting, ceiling fan and an etched glass slider to the rear yard.

The eat-in kitchen has tile flooring, oak cabinets and tile counters and backsplash, and is equipped with:

stainless steel, gas range with self-cleaning oven 
stainless steel dishwasher
double sink with garbage disposal

The master bedroom has laminate flooring, overhead lighting and a walk-in closet. The master bathroom has tile flooring, travertine tile vanity with arched mirror, tile walk-in shower with glass door and a linen closet. The second bedroom has laminate flooring, overhead lighting and a double-door closet. The hall bathroom has a tile flooring, tile shower over tub and a tile vanity with arched mirror.

The fenced rear yard has a covered patio, shed and fruit trees. In the one-car garage there is a laundry area with electric dryer hookup. This home is located in the San Juan Unified School District.

Yard maintenance is tenant responsibility.

As we are first-come first-serve on application processing, you may wish to apply immediately if you think you want to rent this property. description:
Rivercrest offers 328 well-designed apartment homes on a lushly landscaped and waterscaped 20-acre site providing a wealth of amenities. All the spacious residences include private patios/balconies, separate dining areas, walk-in closets, modern gourmet kitchens, storage, and attractive fixtures. Many also offer vaulted ceilings, linen closets, and stylish two-tone decor. Choose from three different floor plans, including 1-bedroom and 2-bedroom apartments as well as 3-bedroom, 2-bath units boasting twin balconies with views. Centrally located in vibrant Sacramento, Rivercrest is only seven miles from downtown, near public bus and light-rail routes, and walking distance to Sacramento State University and the American River greenbelt. 

There are many ways for residents to keep fit and have fun at Rivercrest. They can take advantage of Rivercrest's four swimming pools, heated hydro-spa, four lighted tennis courts, club-like fitness room with TV, basketball and sand volleyball courts, picnic/barbeque area, and children's playground. The club house and resident lounge host a complimentary computer-equipped business center, Wi-Fi connections, billiards, and a free tanning salon and yoga classes. In addition, there are six 24-hour laundry rooms on the premises. 

About Sacramento: Founded during the California Gold Rush, Sacramento is the state's capital and sixth largest city. The Sacramento metro region is home to a diverse population of more than 2.5 million. Higher education institutions in the area include Sacramento State University, the nearby Davis campus of the University of California, three community colleges, Pacific McGeorge School of Law, and a number of private colleges. Among local attractions are the quaint Old Town district, Sutter's Fort Historic Park, the state railroad museum, 5,000 acres of parkland, and numerous cultural and arts activities throughout the year. The Sierra Nevada Gold Country, with its many outdoor recreation destinations and wineries, is just a short drive away.

Near Northrop Avenue and Fulton Avenue in Northrop Estates, Sacramento, this remodeled two-story fourplex offers two bedrooms and one full bathroom. This home has central heat and window air conditioning. The security door entry opens onto all new laminate flooring, dual pane windows with miniblinds and three window air conditioning units throughout 925 square feet of living space. The living room has laminate flooring. There is also a dining area with overhead lighting and ceiling fan.

The eat-in kitchen has laminate flooring, wood cabinets, new granite counters, and is equipped with:

new stainless steel, frost-free refrigerator
electric range with self-cleaning oven 
new stainless steel dishwasher
stainless steel double sink with garbage disposal

The first bedroom is located upstairs and has laminate flooring, mirrored double door closet in the hall and an in-wall air conditioning unit. The second bedroom is located upstairs and has laminate flooring, shutter door closet and an in-wall air conditioning unit. The bathroom has linoleum flooring, tile shower over tub with glass doors, tiled vanity with oak cabinets and a skylight.

The semi-private fenced yard has a covered patio and is equipped with manual sprinklers in front. The shared garage has a designated parking space and designated storage cabinet. The shared laundry room is located at the rear of the building and is equipped with coin-op washer and dryer. This home is located in the San Juan Unified School District, in a community with a swimming pool.

Yard maintenance is owner responsibility.

As we are first-come first-serve on application processing, you may wish to apply immediately if you think you want to rent this property. Security deposit must be received within 24 hours of approved application. You must take possession of the property within two weeks of your approved application. description:
This is a large single story 2 bedroom 2 bath home located in the 55 and over Heritage Park Community in North Natomas. This home features a very spacious living room with formal dining, large kitchen with dining area, den, spacious master suite, 2nd bedroom, hall bathroom and inside laundry room. The front and back yard are fully landscaped and the HOA does the front-yard maintenance! At the Heart of Heritage Park is a 23,000sf club house which boasts many amenities such as a business center, library, game room, theater, ballroom and pub. the fitness center, aerobics room and indoor and outdoor pool are added benefits for those looking to maintain a healthy lifestyle. While the clubhouse is the heart of this community, five one-acre parks make up the soul of Heritage Park. Each park offer different activities such as tennis, basketball, and volleyball courts. you will also find horseshoe pits and areas for badminton and bocce. Tree lined walkways with plenty of room for biking connect each neighborhood and beckon enjoyment of the California sun. Gazebos, fountains, and strategically placed benches allow for reflection and recharging. One small pet will be considered with an additional deposit. This is a no smoking, no vaping home. This home will not take a co-signor. In order to qualify you must have 3 times the monthly rent for income, 2 years of rental references or home ownership and good credit. There is also a monthly utility surcharge of $150 for w/s/g.

description:
Rivercrest offers 328 well-designed apartment homes on a lushly landscaped and waterscaped 20-acre site providing a wealth of amenities. All the spacious residences include private patios/balconies, separate dining areas, walk-in closets, modern gourmet kitchens, storage, and attractive fixtures. Many also offer vaulted ceilings, linen closets, and stylish two-tone decor. Choose from three different floor plans, including 1-bedroom and 2-bedroom apartments as well as 3-bedroom, 2-bath units boasting twin balconies with views. Centrally located in vibrant Sacramento, Rivercrest is only seven miles from downtown, near public bus and light-rail routes, and walking distance to Sacramento State University and the American River greenbelt. 

There are many ways for residents to keep fit and have fun at Rivercrest. They can take advantage of Rivercrest's four swimming pools, heated hydro-spa, four lighted tennis courts, club-like fitness room with TV, basketball and sand volleyball courts, picnic/barbeque area, and children's playground. The club house and resident lounge host a complimentary computer-equipped business center, Wi-Fi connections, billiards, and a free tanning salon and yoga classes. In addition, there are six 24-hour laundry rooms on the premises. 

About Sacramento: Founded during the California Gold Rush, Sacramento is the state's capital and sixth largest city. The Sacramento metro region is home to a diverse population of more than 2.5 million. Higher education institutions in the area include Sacramento State University, the nearby Davis campus of the University of California, three community colleges, Pacific McGeorge School of Law, and a number of private colleges. Among local attractions are the quaint Old Town district, Sutter's Fort Historic Park, the state railroad museum, 5,000 acres of parkland, and numerous cultural and arts activities throughout the year. The Sierra Nevada Gold Country, with its many outdoor recreation destinations and wineries, is just a short drive away.

There are a number of popular amenities at Nepenthe: The clubhouse with two pools, a spa, fitness center and library and a common room with kitchen which is available for rentals. The Dunbarton Cabana which has a pool, a spa, and a party space that is available for rentals. There is also the Elmhurst Pool and there are three sets of tennis courts on the property. This property is located near Hwy 50, Sac State and quick access to Downtown Sacramento.

Pets: Small pet negotiable
Utilities: Tenant pays water, sewer, garbage

You may apply online by clicking APPLY NOW from our website / property listing. Application fee is $35 per adult.

Screening guidelines: All individuals planning on living at the property over the age of 18, must apply.

QUALIFICATIONS:
Four basic items are used as criteria to determine whether a resident will be accepted for a rental home with Residential Equity Management.

1. The total income for the household must be at least 3 times the monthly rent. All income must be lawful and verifiable. We will ask for a current pay stub for each applicant. Other forms of verification may include: IRS 1040 (first 2 pages), court documentation, or county aid documentation.
2. A credit & unlawful detainer check will be ran.
3. Landlord history will be verified for at least the last 2 years & employment verification. Again, if any applicant has had an
eviction, the application will be declined.
4. A credit score of at least 650 is normally required.

Lease terms are (usually) 1 year in length, and renewable at the end of each term upon evaluation of the tenant's payment history, adherence to the terms of the lease & owner approval.

You may apply online by clicking APPLY NOW from our website / property listing. Application fee is $35 per adult.

Screening guidelines: All individuals planning on living at the property over the age of 18, must apply.

QUALIFICATIONS:
Four basic items are used as criteria to determine whether a resident will be accepted for a rental home with Residential Equity Management.

1. The total income for the household must be at least 3 times the monthly rent. All income must be lawful and verifiable. We will ask for a current pay stub for each applicant. Other forms of verification may include: IRS 1040 (first 2 pages), court documentation, or county aid documentation.
2. A credit & unlawful detainer check will be ran.
3. Landlord history will be verified for at least the last 2 years & employment verification. Again, if any applicant has had an
eviction, the application will be declined.
4. A credit score of at least 650 is normally required.

Lease terms are (usually) 1 year in length, and renewable at the end of each term upon evaluation of the tenant's payment history, adherence to the terms of the lease & owner approval.

There are a number of popular amenities at Nepenthe: The clubhouse with two pools, a spa, fitness center and library and a common room with kitchen which is available for rentals. The Dunbarton Cabana which has a pool, a spa, and a party space that is available for rentals. There is also the Elmhurst Pool and there are three sets of tennis courts on the property. This property is located near Hwy 50, Sac State and quick access to Downtown Sacramento. 

Rent $1995
Security deposit $1900
Pets: Small pet negotiable
Utilities: Tenant pays water, sewer, garbage

You may apply online by clicking APPLY NOW from our website / property listing. Application fee is $35 per adult.

Screening guidelines: All individuals planning on living at the property over the age of 18, must apply.

QUALIFICATIONS:
Four basic items are used as criteria to determine whether a resident will be accepted for a rental home with Residential Equity Management.

1. The total income for the household must be at least 3 times the monthly rent. All income must be lawful and verifiable. We will ask for a current pay stub for each applicant. Other forms of verification may include: IRS 1040 (first 2 pages), court documentation, or county aid documentation.
2. A credit & unlawful detainer check will be ran.
3. Landlord history will be verified for at least the last 2 years & employment verification. Again, if any applicant has had an
eviction, the application will be declined.
4. A credit score of at least 650 is normally required.

Lease terms are (usually) 1 year in length, and renewable at the end of each term upon evaluation of the tenant's payment history, adherence to the terms of the lease & owner approval.

description:
Campus Commons - 2 Bdrm, 1 Bath - One story corner unit in desirable Nepenthe - Spacious 2 Bdrm w/ Jack & Jill Bath. Property features an open concept living / dining area, wood burning fireplace, inside laundry, two car garage w/ opener, wood and carpet flooring, vaulted ceilings, private bedrooms and fenced backyard. This property is located in Beautiful Campus Commons Nepenthe Community. 
There are a number of popular amenities at Nepenthe: The clubhouse with two pools, a spa, fitness center and library and a common room with kitchen which is available for rentals. The Dunbarton Cabana which has a pool, a spa, and a party space that is available for rentals. There is also the Elmhurst Pool and there are three sets of tennis courts on the property. This property is located near Hwy 50, Sac State and quick access to Downtown Sacramento. 

Rent $1995
Security deposit $1900
Pets: Small pet negotiable
Utilities: Tenant pays water, sewer, garbage

You may apply online by clicking APPLY NOW from our website / property listing. Application fee is $35 per adult.

Screening guidelines: All individuals planning on living at the property over the age of 18, must apply.

QUALIFICATIONS:
Four basic items are used as criteria to determine whether a resident will be accepted for a rental home with Residential Equity Management.

1. The total income for the household must be at least 3 times the monthly rent. All income must be lawful and verifiable. We will ask for a current pay stub for each applicant. Other forms of verification may include: IRS 1040 (first 2 pages), court documentation, or county aid documentation.
2. A credit & unlawful detainer check will be ran.
3. Landlord history will be verified for at least the last 2 years & employment verification. Again, if any applicant has had an
eviction, the application will be declined.
4. A credit score of at least 650 is normally required.

Lease terms are (usually) 1 year in length, and renewable at the end of each term upon evaluation of the tenant's payment history, adherence to the terms of the lease & owner approval.
*We Do Business in Accordance with State and Federal Fair Housing Laws. It is Illegal to Discriminate Against Any Person Because of Race, Color, Religion, Sex, Handicap, Familial Status or National Origin.

description:
Old Land Park charm meets modern conveniences. Approximately 1750 square foot, 3 Bedroom 2 bath home in Old Land Park for rent. This home is located on the quiet, and centrally located "Brick Street," and a very short walk to award winning Crocker-Riverside Elementary School, California Middle School and CK McClatchy High School. This home boasts a huge yard, .18 acre lot, beautiful, covered brick patio, grass yard, roses and fruit trees with full irrigation, and room for vegetable garden. It also comes with a 2ish car, detached garage.
The home has the original, charming, hard-wood floors and built in cabinets, plus a fully updated kitchen with stainless steel appliances and gas range. The home also has central heat and air, which you may not use much because the brick house stays quite cool in the summer. 
This home also boasts an indoor laundry room with sink and a half basement which is perfect for extra storage. The master bedroom has an en suite bathroom, with a large shower and a walk in closet. The other bathroom has a tub-shower combo. There is also a formal dining room, and a dine-in kitchen nook. If you are looking for a home in Land Park, this may be it! Owner is Real Estate Broker

Four basic items are used as criteria to determine whether a resident will be accepted for a rental home with Residential Equity Management.

Four basic items are used as criteria to determine whether a resident will be accepted for a rental home with Residential Equity Management.

You may apply online by clicking APPLY NOW from our website / property listing. Application fee is $35 per adult.

Screening guidelines: All individuals planning on living at the property over the age of 18, must apply.

QUALIFICATIONS:
Four basic items are used as criteria to determine whether a resident will be accepted for a rental home with Residential Equity Management.

1. The total income for the household must be at least 3 times the monthly rent. All income must be lawful and verifiable. We will ask for a current pay stub for each applicant. Other forms of verification may include: IRS 1040 (first 2 pages), court documentation, or county aid documentation.
2. A credit & unlawful detainer check will be ran.
3. Landlord history will be verified for at least the last 2 years & employment verification. Again, if any applicant has had an
eviction, the application will be declined.
4. A credit score of at least 650 is normally required.

Lease terms are (usually) 1 year in length, and renewable at the end of each term upon evaluation of the tenant's payment history, adherence to the terms of the lease & owner approval.

description:

Property features an open concept living / dining area, wood burning fireplace, inside laundry, two car garage w/ opener, wood and carpet flooring, vaulted ceilings, private bedrooms and fenced backyard. This property is located in Beautiful Campus Commons Nepenthe Community. 
There are a number of popular amenities at Nepenthe: The clubhouse with two pools, a spa, fitness center and library and a common room with kitchen which is available for rentals. The Dunbarton Cabana which has a pool, a spa, and a party space that is available for rentals. There is also the Elmhurst Pool and there are three sets of tennis courts on the property. This property is located near Hwy 50, Sac State and quick access to Downtown Sacramento. 

Rent $1995
Security deposit $1900
Pets: Small pet negotiable
Utilities: Tenant pays water, sewer, garbage

You may apply online by clicking APPLY NOW from our website / property listing. Application fee is $35 per adult.

Screening guidelines: All individuals planning on living at the property over the age of 18, must apply.

QUALIFICATIONS:
Four basic items are used as criteria to determine whether a resident will be accepted for a rental home with Residential Equity Management.

1. The total income for the household must be at least 3 times the monthly rent. All income must be lawful and verifiable. We will ask for a current pay stub for each applicant. Other forms of verification may include: IRS 1040 (first 2 pages), court documentation, or county aid documentation.
2. A credit & unlawful detainer check will be ran.
3. Landlord history will be verified for at least the last 2 years & employment verification. Again, if any applicant has had an
eviction, the application will be declined.
4. A credit score of at least 650 is normally required.

Lease terms are (usually) 1 year in length, and renewable at the end of each term upon evaluation of the tenant's payment history, adherence to the terms of the lease & owner approval.
*We Do Business in Accordance with State and Federal Fair Housing Laws. It is Illegal to Discriminate Against Any Person Because of Race, Color, Religion, Sex, Handicap, Familial Status or National Origin.

description:
Old Land Park charm meets modern conveniences. Approximately 1750 square foot, 3 Bedroom 2 bath home in Old Land Park for rent. This home is located on the quiet, and centrally located "Brick Street," and a very short walk to award winning Crocker-Riverside Elementary School, California Middle School and CK McClatchy High School. This home boasts a huge yard, .18 acre lot, beautiful, covered brick patio, grass yard, roses and fruit trees with full irrigation, and room for vegetable garden. It also comes with a 2ish car, detached garage.
The home has the original, charming, hard-wood floors and built in cabinets, plus a fully updated kitchen with stainless steel appliances and gas range. The home also has central heat and air, which you may not use much because the brick house stays quite cool in the summer. 
This home also boasts an indoor laundry room with sink and a half basement which is perfect for extra storage. The master bedroom has an en suite bathroom, with a large shower and a walk in closet. The other bathroom has a tub-shower combo. There is also a formal dining room, and a dine-in kitchen nook. If you are looking for a home in Land Park, this may be it! Owner is Real Estate Broker
Lease Details: Owner pays for water, trash, city services. Tenant responsible for landscaping and all other utilities. One-year lease preferred, but can be flexible. Security system is optional. Pets are negotiable. Washer, Dryer and Refrigerator are negotiable. This home will be available for occupancy May 1, but could be earlier. If you are interested, please send an e-mail with your phone number, and some information about you. Considering the current situation, we can provide videos, a FaceTime tour, or full access to the house once vacant.

description:
Campus Commons - 2 Bdrm, 1 Bath - One story corner unit in desirable Nepenthe - Spacious 2 Bdrm w/ Jack & Jill Bath. Property features an open concept living / dining area, wood burning fireplace, inside laundry, two car garage w/ opener, wood and carpet flooring, vaulted ceilings, private bedrooms and fenced backyard. This property is located in Beautiful Campus Commons Nepenthe Community. 
There are a number of popular amenities at Nepenthe: The clubhouse with two pools, a spa, fitness center and library and a common room with kitchen which is available for rentals. The Dunbarton Cabana which has a pool, a spa, and a party space that is available for rentals. There is also the Elmhurst Pool and there are three sets of tennis courts on the property. This property is located near Hwy 50, Sac State and quick access to Downtown Sacramento. 

Rent $1995
Security deposit $1900
Pets: Small pet negotiable
Utilities: Tenant pays water, sewer, garbage

You may apply online by clicking APPLY NOW from our website / property listing. Application fee is $35 per adult.

Screening guidelines: All individuals planning on living at the property over the age of 18, must apply.

QUALIFICATIONS:
Four basic items are used as criteria to determine whether a resident will be accepted for a rental home with Residential Equity Management.

1. The total income for the household must be at least 3 times the monthly rent. All income must be lawful and verifiable. We will ask for a current pay stub for each applicant. Other forms of verification may include: IRS 1040 (first 2 pages), court documentation, or county aid documentation.
2. A credit & unlawful detainer check will be ran.
3. Landlord history will be verified for at least the last 2 years & employment verification. Again, if any applicant has had an
eviction, the application will be declined.
4. A credit score of at least 650 is normally required.

Lease terms are (usually) 1 year in length, and renewable at the end of each term upon evaluation of the tenant's payment history, adherence to the terms of the lease & owner approval.
*We Do Business in Accordance with State and Federal Fair Housing Laws. It is Illegal to Discriminate Against Any Person Because of Race, Color, Religion, Sex, Handicap, Familial Status or National Origin.

description:
Old Land Park charm meets modern conveniences. Approximately 1750 square foot, 3 Bedroom 2 bath home in Old Land Park for rent. This home is located on the quiet, and centrally located "Brick Street," and a very short walk to award winning Crocker-Riverside Elementary School, California Middle School and CK McClatchy High School. This home boasts a huge yard, .18 acre lot, beautiful, covered brick patio, grass yard, roses and fruit trees with full irrigation, and room for vegetable garden. It also comes with a 2ish car, detached garage.
The home has the original, charming, hard-wood floors and built in cabinets, plus a fully updated kitchen with stainless steel appliances and gas range. The home also has central heat and air, which you may not use much because the brick house stays quite cool in the summer. 
This home also boasts an indoor laundry room with sink and a half basement which is perfect for extra storage. The master bedroom has an en suite bathroom, with a large shower and a walk in closet. The other bathroom has a tub-shower combo. There is also a formal dining room, and a dine-in kitchen nook. If you are looking for a home in Land Park, this may be it! Owner is Real Estate Broker

Pets: Small pet negotiable

You may apply online by clicking APPLY NOW from our website / property listing. Application fee is $35 per adult.

Screening guidelines: All individuals planning on living at the property over the age of 18, must apply.

QUALIFICATIONS:
Four basic items are used as criteria to determine whether a resident will be accepted for a rental home with Residential Equity Management.

1. The total income for the household must be at least 3 times the monthly rent. All income must be lawful and verifiable. We will ask for a current pay stub for each applicant. Other forms of verification may include: IRS 1040 (first 2 pages), court documentation, or county aid documentation.
2. A credit & unlawful detainer check will be ran.
3. Landlord history will be verified for at least the last 2 years & employment verification. Again, if any applicant has had an
eviction, the application will be declined.
4. A credit score of at least 650 is normally required.

Lease terms are (usually) 1 year in length, and renewable at the end of each term upon evaluation of the tenant's payment history, adherence to the terms of the lease & owner approval.

description:
Campus Commons - 2 Bdrm, 1 Bath - One story corner unit in desirable Nepenthe - Spacious 2 Bdrm w/ Jack & Jill Bath. Property features an open concept living / dining area, wood burning fireplace, inside laundry, two car garage w/ opener, wood and carpet flooring, vaulted ceilings, private bedrooms and fenced backyard. This property is located in Beautiful Campus Commons Nepenthe Community. 
There are a number of popular amenities at Nepenthe: The clubhouse with two pools, a spa, fitness center and library and a common room with kitchen which is available for rentals. The Dunbarton Cabana which has a pool, a spa, and a party space that is available for rentals. There is also the Elmhurst Pool and there are three sets of tennis courts on the property. This property is located near Hwy 50, Sac State and quick access to Downtown Sacramento. 

Rent $1995
Security deposit $1900
Pets: Small pet negotiable
Utilities: Tenant pays water, sewer, garbage

You may apply online by clicking APPLY NOW from our website / property listing. Application fee is $35 per adult.

Screening guidelines: All individuals planning on living at the property over the age of 18, must apply.

QUALIFICATIONS:
Four basic items are used as criteria to determine whether a resident will be accepted for a rental home with Residential Equity Management.

1. The total income for the household must be at least 3 times the monthly rent. All income must be lawful and verifiable. We will ask for a current pay stub for each applicant. Other forms of verification may include: IRS 1040 (first 2 pages), court documentation, or county aid documentation.
2. A credit & unlawful detainer check will be ran.
3. Landlord history will be verified for at least the last 2 years & employment verification. Again, if any applicant has had an
eviction, the application will be declined.
4. A credit score of at least 650 is normally required.

Lease terms are (usually) 1 year in length, and renewable at the end of each term upon evaluation of the tenant's payment history, adherence to the terms of the lease & owner approval.
*We Do Business in Accordance with State and Federal Fair Housing Laws. It is Illegal to Discriminate Against Any Person Because of Race, Color, Religion, Sex, Handicap, Familial Status or National Origin.

description:
Old Land Park charm meets modern conveniences. Approximately 1750 square foot, 3 Bedroom 2 bath home in Old Land Park for rent. This home is located on the quiet, and centrally located "Brick Street," and a very short walk to award winning Crocker-Riverside Elementary School, California Middle School and CK McClatchy High School. This home boasts a huge yard, .18 acre lot, beautiful, covered brick patio, grass yard, roses and fruit trees with full irrigation, and room for vegetable garden. It also comes with a 2ish car, detached garage.
The home has the original, charming, hard-wood floors and built in cabinets, plus a fully updated kitchen with stainless steel appliances and gas range. The home also has central heat and air, which you may not use much because the brick house stays quite cool in the summer. 
This home also boasts an indoor laundry room with sink and a half basement which is perfect for extra storage. The master bedroom has an en suite bathroom, with a large shower and a walk in closet. The other bathroom has a tub-shower combo. There is also a formal dining room, and a dine-in kitchen nook. If you are looking for a home in Land Park, this may be it! Owner is Real Estate Broker
Lease Details: Owner pays for water, trash, city services. Tenant responsible for landscaping and all other utilities. One-year lease preferred, but can be flexible. Security system is optional. Pets are negotiable. Washer, Dryer and Refrigerator are negotiable. This home will be available for occupancy May 1, but could be earlier. If you are interested, please send an e-mail with your phone number, and some information about you. Considering the current situation, we can provide videos, a FaceTime tour, or full access to the house once vacant.

Property features an open concept living / dining area, wood burning fireplace, inside laundry, two car garage w/ opener, wood and carpet flooring, vaulted ceilings, private bedrooms and fenced backyard. This property is located in Beautiful Campus Commons Nepenthe Community. 
There are a number of popular amenities at Nepenthe: The clubhouse with two pools, a spa, fitness center and library and a common room with kitchen which is available for rentals. The Dunbarton Cabana which has a pool, a spa, and a party space that is available for rentals. There is also the Elmhurst Pool and there are three sets of tennis courts on the property. This property is located near Hwy 50, Sac State and quick access to Downtown Sacramento.

Security deposit $1900
Pets: Small pet negotiable
Utilities: Tenant pays water, sewer, garbage

You may apply online by clicking APPLY NOW from our website / property listing. Application fee is $35 per adult.

Screening guidelines: All individuals planning on living at the property over the age of 18, must apply.

QUALIFICATIONS:
Four basic items are used as criteria to determine whether a resident will be accepted for a rental home with Residential Equity Management.

1. The total income for the household must be at least 3 times the monthly rent. All income must be lawful and verifiable. We will ask for a current pay stub for each applicant. Other forms of verification may include: IRS 1040 (first 2 pages), court documentation, or county aid documentation.
2. A credit & unlawful detainer check will be ran.
3. Landlord history will be verified for at least the last 2 years & employment verification. Again, if any applicant has had an
eviction, the application will be declined.
4. A credit score of at least 650 is normally required.

Lease terms are (usually) 1 year in length, and renewable at the end of each term upon evaluation of the tenant's payment history, adherence to the terms of the lease & owner approval.

Screening guidelines: All individuals planning on living at the property over the age of 18, must apply.

QUALIFICATIONS:
Four basic items are used as criteria to determine whether a resident will be accepted for a rental home with Residential Equity Management.

1. The total income for the household must be at least 3 times the monthly rent. All income must be lawful and verifiable. We will ask for a current pay stub for each applicant. Other forms of verification may include: IRS 1040 (first 2 pages), court documentation, or county aid documentation.
2. A credit & unlawful detainer check will be ran.
3. Landlord history will be verified for at least the last 2 years & employment verification. Again, if any applicant has had an
eviction, the application will be declined.
4. A credit score of at least 650 is normally required.

Lease terms are (usually) 1 year in length, and renewable at the end of each term upon evaluation of the tenant's payment history, adherence to the terms of the lease & owner approval.

QUALIFICATIONS:
Four basic items are used as criteria to determine whether a resident will be accepted for a rental home with Residential Equity Management.

1. The total income for the household must be at least 3 times the monthly rent. All income must be lawful and verifiable. We will ask for a current pay stub for each applicant. Other forms of verification may include: IRS 1040 (first 2 pages), court documentation, or county aid documentation.
2. A credit & unlawful detainer check will be ran.
3. Landlord history will be verified for at least the last 2 years & employment verification. Again, if any applicant has had an
eviction, the application will be declined.
4. A credit score of at least 650 is normally required.

description:
Campus Commons - 2 Bdrm, 1 Bath - One story corner unit in desirable Nepenthe - Spacious 2 Bdrm w/ Jack & Jill Bath. Property features an open concept living / dining area, wood burning fireplace, inside laundry, two car garage w/ opener, wood and carpet flooring, vaulted ceilings, private bedrooms and fenced backyard. This property is located in Beautiful Campus Commons Nepenthe Community. 
There are a number of popular amenities at Nepenthe: The clubhouse with two pools, a spa, fitness center and library and a common room with kitchen which is available for rentals. The Dunbarton Cabana which has a pool, a spa, and a party space that is available for rentals. There is also the Elmhurst Pool and there are three sets of tennis courts on the property. This property is located near Hwy 50, Sac State and quick access to Downtown Sacramento. 

Rent $1995
Security deposit $1900
Pets: Small pet negotiable
Utilities: Tenant pays water, sewer, garbage

You may apply online by clicking APPLY NOW from our website / property listing. Application fee is $35 per adult.

Screening guidelines: All individuals planning on living at the property over the age of 18, must apply.

QUALIFICATIONS:
Four basic items are used as criteria to determine whether a resident will be accepted for a rental home with Residential Equity Management.

1. The total income for the household must be at least 3 times the monthly rent. All income must be lawful and verifiable. We will ask for a current pay stub for each applicant. Other forms of verification may include: IRS 1040 (first 2 pages), court documentation, or county aid documentation.
2. A credit & unlawful detainer check will be ran.
3. Landlord history will be verified for at least the last 2 years & employment verification. Again, if any applicant has had an
eviction, the application will be declined.
4. A credit score of at least 650 is normally required.

Lease terms are (usually) 1 year in length, and renewable at the end of each term upon evaluation of the tenant's payment history, adherence to the terms of the lease & owner approval.
*We Do Business in Accordance with State and Federal Fair Housing Laws. It is Illegal to Discriminate Against Any Person Because of Race, Color, Religion, Sex, Handicap, Familial Status or National Origin.

description:
Old Land Park charm meets modern conveniences. Approximately 1750 square foot, 3 Bedroom 2 bath home in Old Land Park for rent. This home is located on the quiet, and centrally located "Brick Street," and a very short walk to award winning Crocker-Riverside Elementary School, California Middle School and CK McClatchy High School. This home boasts a huge yard, .18 acre lot, beautiful, covered brick patio, grass yard, roses and fruit trees with full irrigation, and room for vegetable garden. It also comes with a 2ish car, detached garage.
The home has the original, charming, hard-wood floors and built in cabinets, plus a fully updated kitchen with stainless steel appliances and gas range. The home also has central heat and air, which you may not use much because the brick house stays quite cool in the summer. 
This home also boasts an indoor laundry room with sink and a half basement which is perfect for extra storage. The master bedroom has an en suite bathroom, with a large shower and a walk in closet. The other bathroom has a tub-shower combo. There is also a formal dining room, and a dine-in kitchen nook. If you are looking for a home in Land Park, this may be it! Owner is Real Estate Broker

Pets are negotiable. Washer, Dryer and Refrigerator are negotiable. This home will be available for occupancy May 1, but could be earlier. Considering the current situation, we can provide videos, a FaceTime tour, or full access to the house once vacant.

You may apply online by clicking APPLY NOW from our website / property listing. Application fee is $35 per adult.

Screening guidelines: All individuals planning on living at the property over the age of 18, must apply.

QUALIFICATIONS:
Four basic items are used as criteria to determine whether a resident will be accepted for a rental home with Residential Equity Management.

1. The total income for the household must be at least 3 times the monthly rent. All income must be lawful and verifiable. We will ask for a current pay stub for each applicant. Other forms of verification may include: IRS 1040 (first 2 pages), court documentation, or county aid documentation.
2. A credit & unlawful detainer check will be ran.
3. Landlord history will be verified for at least the last 2 years & employment verification. Again, if any applicant has had an
eviction, the application will be declined.
4. A credit score of at least 650 is normally required.

Lease terms are (usually) 1 year in length, and renewable at the end of each term upon evaluation of the tenant's payment history, adherence to the terms of the lease & owner approval.

Four basic items are used as criteria to determine whether a resident will be accepted for a rental home with Residential Equity Management.

Screening guidelines: All individuals planning on living at the property over the age of 18, must apply.

QUALIFICATIONS:
Four basic items are used as criteria to determine whether a resident will be accepted for a rental home with Residential Equity Management.

1. The total income for the household must be at least 3 times the monthly rent. All income must be lawful and verifiable. We will ask for a current pay stub for each applicant. Other forms of verification may include: IRS 1040 (first 2 pages), court documentation, or county aid documentation.

description:
Campus Commons - 2 Bdrm, 1 Bath - One story corner unit in desirable Nepenthe - Spacious 2 Bdrm w/ Jack & Jill Bath. Property features an open concept living / dining area, wood burning fireplace, inside laundry, two car garage w/ opener, wood and carpet flooring, vaulted ceilings, private bedrooms and fenced backyard. This property is located in Beautiful Campus Commons Nepenthe Community. 
There are a number of popular amenities at Nepenthe: The clubhouse with two pools, a spa, fitness center and library and a common room with kitchen which is available for rentals. The Dunbarton Cabana which has a pool, a spa, and a party space that is available for rentals. There is also the Elmhurst Pool and there are three sets of tennis courts on the property. This property is located near Hwy 50, Sac State and quick access to Downtown Sacramento. 

Rent $1995
Security deposit $1900
Pets: Small pet negotiable
Utilities: Tenant pays water, sewer, garbage

You may apply online by clicking APPLY NOW from our website / property listing. Application fee is $35 per adult.

Screening guidelines: All individuals planning on living at the property over the age of 18, must apply.

QUALIFICATIONS:
Four basic items are used as criteria to determine whether a resident will be accepted for a rental home with Residential Equity Management.

1. The total income for the household must be at least 3 times the monthly rent. All income must be lawful and verifiable. We will ask for a current pay stub for each applicant. Other forms of verification may include: IRS 1040 (first 2 pages), court documentation, or county aid documentation.
2. A credit & unlawful detainer check will be ran.
3. Landlord history will be verified for at least the last 2 years & employment verification. Again, if any applicant has had an
eviction, the application will be declined.
4. A credit score of at least 650 is normally required.

Lease terms are (usually) 1 year in length, and renewable at the end of each term upon evaluation of the tenant's payment history, adherence to the terms of the lease & owner approval.

description:
Old Land Park charm meets modern conveniences. Approximately 1750 square foot, 3 Bedroom 2 bath home in Old Land Park for rent. This home is located on the quiet, and centrally located "Brick Street," and a very short walk to award winning Crocker-Riverside Elementary School, California Middle School and CK McClatchy High School. This home boasts a huge yard, .18 acre lot, beautiful, covered brick patio, grass yard, roses and fruit trees with full irrigation, and room for vegetable garden. It also comes with a 2ish car, detached garage.
The home has the original, charming, hard-wood floors and built in cabinets, plus a fully updated kitchen with stainless steel appliances and gas range. The home also has central heat and air, which you may not use much because the brick house stays quite cool in the summer. 
This home also boasts an indoor laundry room with sink and a half basement which is perfect for extra storage. The master bedroom has an en suite bathroom, with a large shower and a walk in closet. The other bathroom has a tub-shower combo. There is also a formal dining room, and a dine-in kitchen nook. If you are looking for a home in Land Park, this may be it! Owner is Real Estate Broker

Pets are negotiable. Washer, Dryer and Refrigerator are negotiable. This home will be available for occupancy May 1, but could be earlier. description:
Campus Commons - 2 Bdrm, 1 Bath - One story corner unit in desirable Nepenthe - Spacious 2 Bdrm w/ Jack & Jill Bath. Property features an open concept living / dining area, wood burning fireplace, inside laundry, two car garage w/ opener, wood and carpet flooring, vaulted ceilings, private bedrooms and fenced backyard. This property is located in Beautiful Campus Commons Nepenthe Community. 
There are a number of popular amenities at Nepenthe: The clubhouse with two pools, a spa, fitness center and library and a common room with kitchen which is available for rentals. The Dunbarton Cabana which has a pool, a spa, and a party space that is available for rentals. There is also the Elmhurst Pool and there are three sets of tennis courts on the property. This property is located near Hwy 50, Sac State and quick access to Downtown Sacramento. 

Rent $1995
Security deposit $1900
Pets: Small pet negotiable
Utilities: Tenant pays water, sewer, garbage

You may apply online by clicking APPLY NOW from our website / property listing. Application fee is $35 per adult.

Screening guidelines: All individuals planning on living at the property over the age of 18, must apply.

QUALIFICATIONS:
Four basic items are used as criteria to determine whether a resident will be accepted for a rental home with Residential Equity Management.

1. The total income for the household must be at least 3 times the monthly rent. All income must be lawful and verifiable. We will ask for a current pay stub for each applicant. Other forms of verification may include: IRS 1040 (first 2 pages), court documentation, or county aid documentation.
2. A credit & unlawful detainer check will be ran.
3. Landlord history will be verified for at least the last 2 years & employment verification. Again, if any applicant has had an
eviction, the application will be declined.
4. A credit score of at least 650 is normally required.

Lease terms are (usually) 1 year in length, and renewable at the end of each term upon evaluation of the tenant's payment history, adherence to the terms of the lease & owner approval.
*We Do Business in Accordance with State and Federal Fair Housing Laws. It is Illegal to Discriminate Against Any Person Because of Race, Color, Religion, Sex, Handicap, Familial Status or National Origin.

QUALIFICATIONS:
Four basic items are used as criteria to determine whether a resident will be accepted for a rental home with Residential Equity Management.

1. The total income for the household must be at least 3 times the monthly rent. All income must be lawful and verifiable. We will ask for a current pay stub for each applicant. Other forms of verification may include: IRS 1040 (first 2 pages), court documentation, or county aid documentation.
2. A credit & unlawful detainer check will be ran.
3. Landlord history will be verified for at least the last 2 years & employment verification. Again, if any applicant has had an
eviction, the application will be declined.
4. A credit score of at least 650 is normally required.

This home is located on the quiet, and centrally located "Brick Street," and a very short walk to award winning Crocker-Riverside Elementary School, California Middle School and CK McClatchy High School. This home boasts a huge yard, .18 acre lot, beautiful, covered brick patio, grass yard, roses and fruit trees with full irrigation, and room for vegetable garden. It also comes with a 2ish car, detached garage.
The home has the original, charming, hard-wood floors and built in cabinets, plus a fully updated kitchen with stainless steel appliances and gas range. The home also has central heat and air, which you may not use much because the brick house stays quite cool in the summer. 
This home also boasts an indoor laundry room with sink and a half basement which is perfect for extra storage. The master bedroom has an en suite bathroom, with a large shower and a walk in closet. The other bathroom has a tub-shower combo. There is also a formal dining room, and a dine-in kitchen nook. If you are looking for a home in Land Park, this may be it! Owner is Real Estate Broker
Lease Details: Owner pays for water, trash, city services. Tenant responsible for landscaping and all other utilities. One-year lease preferred, but can be flexible. Security system is optional. Pets are negotiable. Washer, Dryer and Refrigerator are negotiable. This home will be available for occupancy May 1, but could be earlier. If you are interested, please send an e-mail with your phone number, and some information about you. Considering the current situation, we can provide videos, a FaceTime tour, or full access to the house once vacant.

description:

Property features an open concept living / dining area, wood burning fireplace, inside laundry, two car garage w/ opener, wood and carpet flooring, vaulted ceilings, private bedrooms and fenced backyard. This property is located in Beautiful Campus Commons Nepenthe Community. 
There are a number of popular amenities at Nepenthe: The clubhouse with two pools, a spa, fitness center and library and a common room with kitchen which is available for rentals. The Dunbarton Cabana which has a pool, a spa, and a party space that is available for rentals. There is also the Elmhurst Pool and there are three sets of tennis courts on the property. This property is located near Hwy 50, Sac State and quick access to Downtown Sacramento. 

Rent $1995
Security deposit $1900
Pets: Small pet negotiable
Utilities: Tenant pays water, sewer, garbage

You may apply online by clicking APPLY NOW from our website / property listing. Application fee is $35 per adult.

Screening guidelines: All individuals planning on living at the property over the age of 18, must apply.

QUALIFICATIONS:
Four basic items are used as criteria to determine whether a resident will be accepted for a rental home with Residential Equity Management.

1. The total income for the household must be at least 3 times the monthly rent. All income must be lawful and verifiable. We will ask for a current pay stub for each applicant. Other forms of verification may include: IRS 1040 (first 2 pages), court documentation, or county aid documentation.
2. A credit & unlawful detainer check will be ran.
3. Landlord history will be verified for at least the last 2 years & employment verification. Again, if any applicant has had an
eviction, the application will be declined.
4. A credit score of at least 650 is normally required.

Lease terms are (usually) 1 year in length, and renewable at the end of each term upon evaluation of the tenant's payment history, adherence to the terms of the lease & owner approval.
*We Do Business in Accordance with State and Federal Fair Housing Laws. It is Illegal to Discriminate Against Any Person Because of Race, Color, Religion, Sex, Handicap, Familial Status or National Origin.

Four basic items are used as criteria to determine whether a resident will be accepted for a rental home with Residential Equity Management.

Four basic items are used as criteria to determine whether a resident will be accepted for a rental home with Residential Equity Management.

You may apply online by clicking APPLY NOW from our website / property listing. Application fee is $35 per adult.

Screening guidelines: All individuals planning on living at the property over the age of 18, must apply.

QUALIFICATIONS:
Four basic items are used as criteria to determine whether a resident will be accepted for a rental home with Residential Equity Management.

1. The total income for the household must be at least 3 times the monthly rent. All income must be lawful and verifiable. We will ask for a current pay stub for each applicant. Other forms of verification may include: IRS 1040 (first 2 pages), court documentation, or county aid documentation.
2. A credit & unlawful detainer check will be ran.
3. Landlord history will be verified for at least the last 2 years & employment verification. Again, if any applicant has had an
eviction, the application will be declined.
4. A credit score of at least 650 is normally required.

Lease terms are (usually) 1 year in length, and renewable at the end of each term upon evaluation of the tenant's payment history, adherence to the terms of the lease & owner approval.

description:

Property features an open concept living / dining area, wood burning fireplace, inside laundry, two car garage w/ opener, wood and carpet flooring, vaulted ceilings, private bedrooms and fenced backyard. This property is located in Beautiful Campus Commons Nepenthe Community. 
There are a number of popular amenities at Nepenthe: The clubhouse with two pools, a spa, fitness center and library and a common room with kitchen which is available for rentals. The Dunbarton Cabana which has a pool, a spa, and a party space that is available for rentals. There is also the Elmhurst Pool and there are three sets of tennis courts on the property. This property is located near Hwy 50, Sac State and quick access to Downtown Sacramento. 

Rent $1995
Security deposit $1900
Pets: Small pet negotiable
Utilities: Tenant pays water, sewer, garbage

You may apply online by clicking APPLY NOW from our website / property listing. Application fee is $35 per adult.

Screening guidelines: All individuals planning on living at the property over the age of 18, must apply.

QUALIFICATIONS:
Four basic items are used as criteria to determine whether a resident will be accepted for a rental home with Residential Equity Management.

1. The total income for the household must be at least 3 times the monthly rent. All income must be lawful and verifiable. We will ask for a current pay stub for each applicant. Other forms of verification may include: IRS 1040 (first 2 pages), court documentation, or county aid documentation.
2. A credit & unlawful detainer check will be ran.
3. Landlord history will be verified for at least the last 2 years & employment verification. Again, if any applicant has had an
eviction, the application will be declined.
4. A credit score of at least 650 is normally required.

Lease terms are (usually) 1 year in length, and renewable at the end of each term upon evaluation of the tenant's payment history, adherence to the terms of the lease & owner approval.
*We Do Business in Accordance with State and Federal Fair Housing Laws. It is Illegal to Discriminate Against Any Person Because of Race, Color, Religion, Sex, Handicap, Familial Status or National Origin.

description:
Old Land Park charm meets modern conveniences. Approximately 1750 square foot, 3 Bedroom 2 bath home in Old Land Park for rent. This home is located on the quiet, and centrally located "Brick Street," and a very short walk to award winning Crocker-Riverside Elementary School, California Middle School and CK McClatchy High School. This home boasts a huge yard, .18 acre lot, beautiful, covered brick patio, grass yard, roses and fruit trees with full irrigation, and room for vegetable garden. It also comes with a 2ish car, detached garage.
The home has the original, charming, hard-wood floors and built in cabinets, plus a fully updated kitchen with stainless steel appliances and gas range. The home also has central heat and air, which you may not use much because the brick house stays quite cool in the summer. 
This home also boasts an indoor laundry room with sink and a half basement which is perfect for extra storage. The master bedroom has an en suite bathroom, with a large shower and a walk in closet. The other bathroom has a tub-shower combo. There is also a formal dining room, and a dine-in kitchen nook. If you are looking for a home in Land Park, this may be it! Owner is Real Estate Broker
Lease Details: Owner pays for water, trash, city services. Tenant responsible for landscaping and all other utilities. One-year lease preferred, but can be flexible. Security system is optional. Pets are negotiable. Washer, Dryer and Refrigerator are negotiable. This home will be available for occupancy May 1, but could be earlier. If you are interested, please send an e-mail with your phone number, and some information about you. Considering the current situation, we can provide videos, a FaceTime tour, or full access to the house once vacant.
